#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:1
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "lesson.title"
msgid "Introduction to Member Variables"
msgstr "认识成员变量"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:13
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In this lesson, we take a first look at variables."
msgstr "在本节课中，我们首次接触变量。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:14
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In games, you need to keep track of many values that change over time:"
msgstr "在游戏中，你需要追踪许多会随时间变化的值："

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:15
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid ""
"- The player's score.\n"
"- Every character or enemy's health.\n"
"- The last checkpoint."
msgstr ""
"- 玩家的得分。\n"
"- 每个角色或敌人的生命值。\n"
"- 上一个检查点。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:16
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "And so much more. You need to store, retrieve, and update those values."
msgstr "还有很多很多。你需要存储、读取和更新这些值。"

#. TRANSLATORS: The "term" in [glossary term="<term>"] should NOT be translated here
#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:17
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "We call those values [i][glossary term=\"variables\"][/i]. Variables are labels you use to keep track of values that vary over time. Here's an example of a variable tracking a character or monster's health."
msgstr "我们把这些值称为 [i]变量[/i] （variable）。变量就是用来追踪随时间变化的值的标签。下面是一个追踪角色或怪物生命值的变量示例。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:21
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "The line above defines a new variable named [code]health[/code] and assigns it a starting value of [code]100[/code] (that's what the equal sign does, more on that below)."
msgstr "定义一个名为 [code]health[/code] 的变量，其起始值为 [code]100[/code]。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:22
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Function parameters, which you saw in the previous lesson, are another example of variables."
msgstr "你在上一课中见过的函数参数，也是变量的一种。"

#. TRANSLATORS: The "term" in [glossary term="<term>"] should NOT be translated here
#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:23
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In this lesson, we start using variables built into Godot. They're a particular kind called [i][glossary term=\"member variables\"][/i]."
msgstr "本课中，我们从使用 Godot 内置的变量开始。它们是一种特殊的类型，叫做 [i]成员变量[/i] （member variable）。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:24
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Member variables are values attached to a game entity. They're useful properties like the [code]position[/code], [code]rotation[/code], and [code]scale[/code] of a character."
msgstr "成员变量是附加到游戏实体上的值。它们是非常实用的属性，比如角色的 [code]position[/code] （位置）、[code]rotation[/code]（旋转）和 [code]scale[/code] （缩放）。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:25
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In a previous lesson, we saw how we could use the [code]rotate()[/code] function to rotate our character."
msgstr "在前面的课程中，我们看到了如何用 [code]rotate()[/code] 函数来旋转角色。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:37
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This function increases or decreases the value of the entity's [code]rotation[/code] member variable."
msgstr "这个函数会增大或减小实体的 [code]rotation[/code] 成员变量的值。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:38
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Say we want to reset the rotation to [code]0[/code] and make the character upright. Using the [code]rotate()[/code] function can prove difficult: you need to know the character's exact current angle to cancel it out."
msgstr "假设我们想把旋转重置为 [code]0[/code]，让角色恢复直立。用 [code]rotate()[/code] 函数来做这件事可能会很麻烦：你得知道角色当前的确切角度，才能将其抵消。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:39
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It's much easier to use the member variable rather than the function."
msgstr "直接用成员变量比用函数要简单得多。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:40
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "The following code assigns the value [code]0[/code] to the character's rotation, resetting its angle and making it upright."
msgstr "下面的代码将值 [code]0[/code] 赋给了角色的旋转属性，从而重置角度，让角色恢复直立。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:41
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Notice how we use the equal sign ([code]=[/code]) to change the value of a variable."
msgstr "请注意，我们不需要重复写 [code]var[/code] 关键字，因为我们只需要它来 [i]定义[/i] 一个变量。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:41
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "quiz.0.question"
msgid "What's a variable?"
msgstr "什么是变量？"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:41
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "quiz.0.explanation"
msgid "Variables are labels you use to access values that change over time."
msgstr "变量是你用来访问那些会随时间变化的值的标签。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:41
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "quiz.0.explanation"
msgid "You can also use them to put a name on a value you want to reuse throughout your code. It makes your code easier to read and to change."
msgstr "你也可以用变量来给代码中反复出现的值起个名字。这样代码会更易读、也更容易修改。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:41
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "quiz.0.answer.valid"
msgid "A label you use to keep track of a value that can change."
msgstr "一种用来追踪可变值的标签。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:41
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "quiz.0.answer"
msgid "A function that varies over time."
msgstr "一种随时间变化的函数。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:41
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "quiz.0.answer"
msgid "A decimal number."
msgstr "一个小数。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:50
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "Accessing sub-variables with the dot"
msgstr "用点号访问子变量"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:62
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In video games, you will see many member variables that have sub-values."
msgstr "在电子游戏中，你会看到很多成员变量都带有子属性。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:63
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "For example, the [code]position[/code] we mentioned has two coordinates: [code]x[/code] and [code]y[/code]."
msgstr "比如我们刚才提到的 [code]position[/code]，它就包含两个坐标：[code]x[/code] 和 [code]y[/code]。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:64
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It's the same for the [code]scale[/code]: it has [code]x[/code] and [code]y[/code] sub-variables. They respectively control the horizontal and vertical size of the game entity."
msgstr "[code]scale[/code] 也是一样：它也有 [code]x[/code] 和 [code]y[/code] 两个子变量，分别控制游戏实体的横向和纵向大小。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:65
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "To access those X and Y sub-components, you add a dot (\".\") after the variable name."
msgstr "要访问这些 X 和 Y 子组件，在变量名后面加一个点号（.）就行。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:66
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "The code below places the entity at [code]200[/code] pixels on the x-axis and [code]250[/code] pixels on the y-axis."
msgstr "下面的代码将实体放在 x 轴上 [code]200[/code] 像素、y 轴上 [code]250[/code] 像素的位置。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:70
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Notice how we use the equal sign (\"=\") to assign the numbers on the right to the sub-variables on the left."
msgstr "注意我们是怎样用等号（=）把右边的数值赋给左边的子变量的。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:71
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Unlike in maths, in computer programming, the equal sign (\"=\") does not mean \"is equal to.\""
msgstr "和数学不同，在计算机编程中，等号（=）并不表示\"等于\"。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:72
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Instead, it means \"assign the result of the expression on the right to the variable on the left\". We assign values so often in code that we prefer to reserve the equal sign for that."
msgstr "它的意思是\"把右边表达式的结果赋给左边的变量\"。代码中赋值的操作非常频繁，所以我们选择把等号留给这个用途。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:70
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "In games, the Y-axis is positive going down"
msgstr "在游戏中，Y 轴向下为正"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:78
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Note that in games, assuming your character's position starts at (0, 0), the code above moves the entity [code]200[/code] pixels to the right and [code]250[/code] pixels down."
msgstr "请注意，在游戏中，假设角色初始位置是 (0, 0)，那么上面的代码会将实体向右移动 [code]200[/code] 像素、向下移动 [code]250[/code] 像素。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:79
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In math, the y-axis is generally positive going up by convention."
msgstr "数学中按惯例，y 轴通常是向上为正的。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:80
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "The convention is the [i]opposite[/i] in video games and many computer applications: the y-axis is positive going down."
msgstr "而在电子游戏和许多计算机应用中，这个约定是[i]反过来的[/i]：y 轴向下为正。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:80
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "note.title"
msgid "Why does the Y-axis point downwards?"
msgstr "为什么 Y 轴是向下的？"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:81
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "note.text"
msgid "This may be confusing if you only saw the y-axis pointing up in math classes. However, in math, axes go in any direction. They don't even have to be perpendicular."
msgstr "如果你在数学课上只见过 y 轴向上，可能会觉得有点困惑。但数学中，坐标轴其实可以指向任意方向，甚至不必互相垂直。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:82
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "note.text"
msgid "On the computer, the position (0, 0) happens to correspond to the top-left of your computer screen. It then makes sense for coordinates to be positive when going towards the bottom-right corner."
msgstr "在计算机中，(0, 0) 这个位置恰好对应屏幕的左上角。这样一来，朝着右下角的方向坐标为正就说得通了。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:83
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "note.text"
msgid "This leads to another question: why is position zero the top left of the screen? This is due to computer and TV displays history: they would calculate and display pixels starting from the top left corner and moving towards the bottom right corner."
msgstr "这又引出另一个问题：为什么零点在屏幕左上角？这源于计算机和电视显示器的历史：它们会从左上角开始计算并渲染像素，逐行往右下角推进。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:90
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let's look at one last example before moving on to the practice. The following code makes the character 1.5 times its starting size."
msgstr "进入练习之前，来看最后一个例子。下面的代码会让角色变为原始大小的 1.5 倍。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:92
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "quiz.1.question"
msgid "How do you access sub-variables?"
msgstr "如何访问子变量？"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:92
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "quiz.1.content"
msgid "Variables often hold sub-values, like the [code]position[/code] has two sub-variables: [code]x[/code] and [code]y[/code]. How would you access the [code]x[/code], for example?"
msgstr "变量通常会包含子值，比如 [code]position[/code] 就有两个子变量：[code]x[/code] 和 [code]y[/code]。那么，该如何访问其中的 [code]x[/code] 呢？"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:92
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "quiz.1.explanation"
msgid "To access a sub-variable, you need to write a dot between the parent variable name and the sub-variable name."
msgstr "要访问子变量，需要在父变量名和子变量名之间写一个点号。"

#: course/lesson-7-member-variables/lesson.bbcode:92
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "quiz.1.explanation"
msgid "For example, to access the [code]x[/code] sub-variable of the [code]position[/code] variable, you'll write [code]position.x[/code]."
