#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:16
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "For example, the [code]round()[/code] function takes a decimal number as an argument and gives you back a new whole number rounded to the nearest digit."
msgstr "例如，[code]round()[/code] 函数接受一个小数作为参数，并返回一个四舍五入到最接近整数的新整数。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:21
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Imagine you have a game where you track the player's health as a percentage, a decimal number going from [code]0.0[/code] to [code]100.0[/code]."
msgstr "想象一下，你在做一个游戏，以百分比的形式跟踪玩家的生命值，这个百分比是一个从 [code]0.0[/code] 到 [code]100.0[/code] 的小数。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:22
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "When displaying the health on the interface, you don't want to show the decimal part. In that case, you may use the [code]round()[/code] function, like so."
msgstr "在游戏界面上显示生命值时，你不想显示出小数部分。在这种情况下，你可以可以像这样使用 [code]round()[/code] 函数。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:27
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Notice how we assign the result of the function call to a variable. Because the [code]round()[/code] function returns a [i]new[/i] value, we need to either store the result in a variable or use the value immediately."
msgstr "注意我们如何将函数调用的结果赋值给一个变量。因为[code]round()[/code]函数返回一个[i]新[/i]值，我们需要将结果存储在变量中或立即使用该值。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:28
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Above, we assigned it to a variable, but you could also do the following."
msgstr "在上面的例子里，我们将结果赋值给了一个变量，但你也可以像下面这样做。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:31
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If you need to use a returned value more than once, store it in a variable first. Otherwise, you can use the function call directly where you need it."
msgstr "如果你需要多次使用返回的值，请先将其存储在变量中。否则，你可以在需要的地方直接调用函数。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:31
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "A cooler example: lerp()"
msgstr "更酷的例子：lerp()函数"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:41
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "The [code]lerp()[/code] function (short for [i]linear interpolate[/i]), blends between two values."
msgstr "[code]jump()[/code] 函数捡起海龟并将其放置在相对位置上。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:42
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It takes three arguments: a start value, an end value, and a blend amount between [code]0.0[/code] and [code]1.0[/code] that controls the blend. A value of [code]0.0[/code] gives you the start value, [code]1.0[/code] gives you the end value, and [code]0.5[/code] gives you halfway between them."
msgstr "它有三个参数：一个开始值，一个结束值，以及一个介于[code]0.0[/code]和[code]1.0[/code]之间的混合量，用于控制混合。当混合量为[code]0.0[/code]时，得到起始值；[code]1.0[/code]时得到结束值；[code]0.5[/code]时得到两者之间的中间值。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:43
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In games, [code]lerp()[/code] is often used to make things move smoothly towards a target."
msgstr "在游戏中，[code]lerp()[/code] 通常用于使物体平滑地向目标移动。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:44
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "[b]Note:[/b] In the code example below, I wrote the [code]lerp()[/code] function call across multiple lines for readability. This works exactly the same as writing it on one line."
msgstr "[b]注意：[/b]为了提高可读性，在下面的代码示例中我将`lerp()`函数调用写成了多行。这与将其写在一行上效果完全相同。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:49
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Every frame, the code calculates a position somewhere between the turtle and the mouse cursor. The [code]lerp()[/code] function takes care of everything."
msgstr "每一帧，代码都会计算海龟和鼠标光标之间的某个位置。[code]lerp()[/code]函数会处理好一切。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:50
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It's not the most robust approach for smooth movement, as you'll learn in the future, but it's a helpful function nonetheless."
msgstr "虽然这不是实现平滑移动最健壮的方法——你将来会学到——但它仍然是一个有用的函数。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:49
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "Writing a function that returns a value"
msgstr "定义函数时，参数是..."

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:63
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You can make [i]your[/i] functions return values."
msgstr "你可以让 [i]你的[/i] 函数也能返回值。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:64
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "To make a function return a value, you use the [code]return[/code] keyword followed by the value in question."
msgstr "在函数定义中，[code]func[/code] 关键字和函数名之间必须有一个空格。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:65
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In previous lessons, we had characters walking on grids. For those practices, you were working with cell coordinates like [code]Vector2(0, 0)[/code] or [code]Vector2(2, 1)[/code]."
msgstr "在之前的课程中，我们让角色在网格上行走。在那些练习中，你使用的是像[code]Vector2(0, 0)[/code]或[code]Vector2(2, 1)[/code]这样的单元格坐标。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:66
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "But cell coordinates are not the same as positions on the screen. A cell coordinate like [code]Vector2(2, 1)[/code] tells us which cell we're in, but not where it is in pixels. To draw something on screen, we need pixel positions."
msgstr "但是单元格坐标与屏幕上的位置并不相同。像[code]Vector2(2, 1)[/code]这样的单元格坐标告诉我们当前所在的单元格，但并不能告诉我们它在像素中的具体位置。要在屏幕上绘制内容，我们需要像素位置。"

#: course/lesson-22-functions-return-values/lesson.bbcode:67
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "We can write a function to convert cell coordinates to pixel positions. Hover over the cells below to see how it works."
