#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:1
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "lesson.title"
msgid "Value types"
msgstr "值类型"

#. TRANSLATORS: The "term" in [glossary term="<term>"] should NOT be translated here
#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In your code, values have a particular [glossary term=\"type\"]. You have already learned about several: whole numbers, decimal numbers, strings, 2D vectors, arrays, and dictionaries."
msgstr "在你的代码中，不同的值是有特定的[i]类型[/i]的。 其实你已经见过了这几种：整数、小数、字符串、二维向量、数组还有字典。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "The computer uses the type of a value to know which operations and functions you can use with them."
msgstr "计算机用值类型才能分清楚，可以对这些值使用哪些操作和函数。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:5
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "As a result, it's essential to understand types: they are not fully compatible with one another, and misusing them will cause errors."
msgstr "因此，了解值类型至关重要：它们彼此不完全兼容，滥用乱用会导致错误。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:9
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "A prime example"
msgstr "一个典型的例子"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:13
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You want to display the player's health in the interface. Your code tracks health as a whole number, a value of type [code]int[/code] (short for integer)."
msgstr "假设你想在游戏界面中显示玩家的生命值。你的代码将生命值作为一个整数追踪，一个[code]int[/code]类型的值（整数integer的缩写）。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:19
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "However, to display it on the player's screen, the computer wants text: it needs a value of type [code]String[/code]."
msgstr "但是呢，为了在玩家的屏幕上显示它，计算机需要的是字符文本：它需要一个[code]String[/code]（字符串）类型的值。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:20
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You can concatenate two strings with the [code]+[/code] operator."
msgstr "你可以用 [code]+[/code] 运算符连接两个字符串。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:23
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "So the following code looks like it could work at first glance."
msgstr "举一反三，下面的代码乍一看似乎可以工作。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:27
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "But when running the code, we get this strange error."
msgstr "但是在运行代码时，我们得到了这个奇怪的报错。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:33
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It tells you that you can't add values of type [code]String[/code] and [code]int[/code]: they're incompatible."
msgstr "它意思是，不能将 [code]String[/code] 和 [code]int[/code] 类型的值加在一块：它们不兼容。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:34
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In that case, you need to convert the [code]health[/code] number into a [code]String[/code]."
msgstr "在这种情况下，需要你先把 [code]health[/code] 数字转换为 [code]String[/code]。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:33
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "Converting values into strings"
msgstr "将其他类型的值转换为字符串"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:39
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You can get the text representation of a value by calling the [code]str()[/code] function (short for \"string\"). The function returns its argument as a new [code]String[/code]."
msgstr "可以通过调用 [code]str()[/code] 函数（“String”的缩写）来获取其他类型的值的文本形式。 该函数将其参数转成一个新的 [code]String[/code] 返回。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:40
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You can use this function whenever you want to turn some number or vector into text."
msgstr "每当你想把某个数字或向量转换为文本时，都可以使用此功能。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:43
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In this case, it turns the number [code]100[/code] into the string [code]\"100\"[/code]. Or whatever number [code]health[/code] is currently."
msgstr "此代码将值 [code]100[/code] 分配给名为 [code]health[/code] 的新创建的变量。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:43
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "Converting strings into numbers"
msgstr "将字符串转换为数字"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:49
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You can also convert strings into whole numbers or decimal numbers using respectively the [code]int()[/code] and [code]float()[/code] functions."
msgstr "你还可以分别使用 [code]int()[/code]或[code]float()[/code]函数将字符串转换为整数或小数。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:50
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Those functions can convert what the player writes in a text field into a number. For example, the number of potions to sell at once in a shop."
msgstr "这些函数可以将玩家在文本字段中写入的内容转换为数字。 例如，玩家在商店中一次性出售的药水数量。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:51
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "Some types are partially compatible"
msgstr "某些值类型能部分兼容"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:57
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Most types are incompatible. For example, you can't directly add or multiply an array with a number."
msgstr "大多数值类型互不兼容。 例如，不能直接将数组与数字相加或相乘。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:58
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "However, some types are [i]partially[/i] compatible. For example, you can multiply or divide a vector by a number."
msgstr "但是，某些值类型能[i]部分[/i]兼容。例如，你可以将向量乘以或除以一个数字。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:63
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It is possible because other developers defined that operation for you under the hood."
msgstr "这是可行的，因为其他开发人员已经在后台帮你定义了这种操作。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:64
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "However, you cannot directly add or subtract a number to a vector. You'll get an error. That's why, in earlier lessons, you had to access the sub-variables of [code]position[/code] to add numbers to them."
msgstr "但是，不能直接让向量和数字加减。会报错。 这就是为什么在前面的课程中，你必须访问 [code]position[/code] 的子变量x和y来分别为它们加上数字。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:63
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "A surprising result"
msgstr "出人意料的结果"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:67
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Take the following division: [code]3/2[/code]. What result would you expect to get? [code]1.5[/code]?"
msgstr "以这个除法为例：[code]3/2[/code]。你觉得会得到什么结果？[code]1.5[/code]？"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:77
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Well, for the computer, the result of [code]3/2[/code] is [code]1[/code]."
msgstr "嘿嘿（意味深长），对于计算机来说，[code]3/2[/code] 的结果是 [code]1[/code]。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:78
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Wait, what?!"
msgstr "啊，啊？！"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:79
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "That's because, for the computer, the division of two whole numbers should always result in a whole number."
msgstr "那是因为，对于计算机来说，两个整数相除结果只应该是一个整数。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:80
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "When you divide decimal numbers instead, you will get a decimal number as a result."
msgstr "将小数相除的话，结果才会是一个小数。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:83
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Even if it's just a [code]0[/code], adding a decimal place tells the computer we want decimal numbers."
msgstr "就算只是多了一个 [code]0[/code]，添加一个小数位也会告诉计算机我们用的是小数。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:84
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This shows you how mindful you need to be with types. Otherwise, you will get unexpected results. It can get pretty serious: number errors can lead to bugs like controls not working as intended or charging the wrong price to players."
msgstr "这个例子可以看出，你应当对值类型有很高的关注度。否则，你会得到各种意料之外的结果。问题可能会变得非常严重：数字错误会导致各种bug，例如如控件无法正常工作，或商店要价出错让玩家买单等等。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:83
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "Understanding and mastering types is a key skill for developers"
msgstr "理解和掌握值类型是开发人员的必备技能"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:93
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Programming beginners often struggle due to the lack of understanding of types."
msgstr "由于缺乏对值类型的理解，编程初学者经常遇到各种困难。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:94
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Languages like GDScript hide the types from you by default. As a result, if you don't understand that some are incompatible, you can get stuck when facing type-related errors."
msgstr "默认情况下，像 GDScript 这样的语言会试着隐藏类型（弱类型语言）。结果是，如果你不了解某些不能兼容的细节，在遇到值类型相关的错误时可能会卡住。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:95
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You'll want to keep that in mind in your learning journey. When writing code, you will need to understand everything that's happening."
msgstr "你需要在学习过程中牢记这一点。编写代码时，最好能弄明白正在发生的一切的原理。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:96
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "That said, let's practice some type conversions."
msgstr "总而言之，让我们做点类型转换的练习。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:93
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.0.title"
msgid "Displaying the player's health and energy"
msgstr "显示玩家的生命值和能量值"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:93
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.0.goal"
msgid "We want to display the player's energy in the user interface."
msgstr "我们希望在UI界面中显示玩家的能量值。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:93
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.0.goal"
msgid "Currently, our code has a type error. We're trying to display a whole number while the [code]display_energy()[/code] function expects a string."
msgstr "目前，我们的代码存在值类型错误。它试图显示一个整数，而 [code]display_energy()[/code]（显示能量值）函数需要一个字符串。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:93
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.0.goal"
msgid "Using the [code]str()[/code] function, clear the type error and make the energy amount display on the interface."
msgstr "使用[code]str()[/code]函数，清除类型错误，在界面上显示出能量值。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:93
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.0.goal"
msgid "You can't change the [code]energy[/code] variable definition: setting it to [code]\"80\"[/code] would break the rest of the game's code. You must convert the value when calling [code]display_energy()[/code]."
msgstr "不能更改 [code]energy[/code] 变量的类型定义：将其设置为 [code]\"80\"[/code] 会破坏游戏的其它代码。调用 [code]display_energy()[/code] 时必须转换值。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:93
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.0.description"
msgid "We want to display the player's energy in the interface but face a type error. Use your new knowledge to fix it."
msgstr "我们想在界面中显示玩家的能量值，但是遇到了类型错误。用你学到的新知识来修复它。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:116
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.1.title"
msgid "Letting the player type numbers"
msgstr "让玩家输入数字"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:116
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.1.goal"
msgid "In our game's shops, we want to let the player type numbers to select the number of items they want to buy or sell."
msgstr "在我们的游戏商店中，我们想让玩家输入数字来选择他们想要购买或出售的物品的数量。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:116
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.1.goal"
msgid "We need to know the number of items as an [code]int[/code], but the computer reads the player's input as a [code]String[/code]."
msgstr "我们需要以 [code]int[/code] 的形式得到物品的数量，但计算机将玩家的输入读取为[code]String[/code]字符。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:116
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.1.goal"
msgid "Your task is to convert the player's input into numbers for the shop's code to work."
msgstr "你的任务是将玩家输入的字符串转换为数字，以便商店的代码能够正常工作。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:116
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.1.goal"
msgid "Using the [code]int()[/code] function, convert the player's input into a whole number and store the result in the [code]item_count[/code] variable."
msgstr "补全 [code]take_damage()[/code] 函数，让它能把 定义好的[code]health[/code]变量减去[code]amount[/code]点。"

#: course/lesson-27-value-types/lesson.bbcode:116
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.1.description"
msgid "We want the player to choose the number of items they buy or sell in our game's shops. But right now, all we get are type errors."
msgstr "我们想让玩家决定他们在游戏商店中购买或出售的物品的数量。但是现在，我们有的只是类型错误。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:1
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "lesson.title"
msgid "Specifying types with type hints"
msgstr "用类型提示功能指定变量类型"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:7
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "By default, GDScript is what we call a dynamically-typed language. That means that you can just write variables, assign them a value with a number, and assign them another value with a different type."
msgstr "默认情况下，GDScript 是我们常说的动态类型（dynamically-typed）语言。 这意味着你写变量的时候，给它分配一个数字类型的值也可以，然后重新分配一个不同类型的值也可以。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:8
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Unlike in some other languages, in GDScript, the following code is valid."
msgstr "与其他一些语言不同，在GDScript中，以下代码是有效的。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:11
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "But this feature often causes problems down the line. Let's take one example."
msgstr "但是这个特性通常会导致问题。举个例子。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:11
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "Cell size: decimal number, or 2D vector?"
msgstr "格子的大小：是小数还是二维向量？"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:21
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Games use grids all the time, be it for grid-based gameplay or to make algorithms faster."
msgstr "游戏总会用到各种网格，无论是基于网格实现各种玩法，还是用网格让算法更快速。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:22
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "When working with grids, you need to convert grid coordinates into positions in the game world all the time. To do so, you give each cell a size in pixels."
msgstr "使用网格时，始终得将网格坐标转换为游戏世界的坐标。 为此，需要为单元格设定好它的像素大小。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:23
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You'll likely pick one of two types for that: [code]float[/code] or [code]Vector2[/code], because pixel positions on the screen use [code]Vector2[/code] coordinates."
msgstr "为此你可能会用到以下两种类型的一种：[code]float[/code] 或 [code]Vector2[/code]，因为屏幕上的像素位置用的也是[code]Vector2[/code]坐标。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:24
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Either of those two values would be fine:"
msgstr "这两种类型的值都可以："

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:25
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Using a [code]Vector2[/code] could simplify some calculations. For example, when converting grid coordinates to game world coordinates."
msgstr "使用 [code]Vector2[/code] 能简化一些计算。 例如，将网格坐标转换为游戏世界坐标时。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:31
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In this example, because both [code]cell[/code] and [code]cell_size[/code] are [code]Vector2[/code] values, we can add them."
msgstr "在这个例子中，因为 [code]cell[/code] 和 [code]cell_size[/code] 都是 [code]Vector2[/code] 值，可以直接相加。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:32
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "However, if [code]cell_size[/code] is a [code]float[/code], we will get a type error."
msgstr "但是，如果 [code]cell_size[/code] 是 [code]float[/code]型，就会得到类型错误。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:39
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Worse: due to dynamic typing, we won't get an error [i]right away[/i]. We will only get the error when calling [code]grid_to_world(Vector2(1, 1))[/code]."
msgstr "更糟糕的是：由于类型可以动态变化，不会[i]写完就提示错误[/i]。在你调用 [code]grid_to_world(Vector2(1, 1))[/code]时才会得到错误。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:40
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "And that's a big problem."
msgstr "这是一个大问题。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:45
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Because we're learning, we only have small code examples in this course. But your games' code will get long and split into many files. When coding, you often forget about the code you wrote several weeks ago."
msgstr "因为我们正在学习，在本课程中的代码示例都是小体量的。但你的游戏代码会变得很长，并且拆分成许多个文件。敲代码时，忘记几周前写了啥代码是很寻常的。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:46
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "And with a lot of code, it could take [i]hours[/i] of play before players trigger a type error in your code."
msgstr "也就是说在成吨代码里，尽管错误已经发生了，玩家可能还要玩[i]好几个小时[/i]，类型错误才会被触发。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:45
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "Using type hints"
msgstr "使用类型提示功能"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:53
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Fortunately, GDScript has optional [i]type hints[/i]."
msgstr "幸运的是，GDScript有可选的[i] 类型提示 [/i]功能。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:54
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Type hints let the computer know the value type you want for variables and report errors before running the code."
msgstr "使用类型提示功能，计算机就能知道你想要的值类型，并在运行代码之前就报告错误。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:55
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "To specify the type a variable can accept, you can write a colon and a type after the name when defining a new variable."
msgstr "要指定某个变量可以接受的类型，在定义新变量时要在变量名称后写一个冒号和一个类型名。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:57
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You could tell the computer you want [code]cell_size[/code] only to accept [code]Vector2[/code] values like so."
msgstr "你可以告诉计算机，你想让 [code]cell_size[/code] 只接受 [code]Vector2[/code]类型的值，像下面这样。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:61
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If you try to replace the [code]cell_size[/code] with a value of another type later, the computer will not let you."
msgstr "如果你写着写着将 [code]cell_size[/code] 替换为了其他类型的值，计算机不会允许你这么做。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:65
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "Letting the computer figure it out"
msgstr "让电脑自己搞清楚"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:71
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "GDScript comes with a feature called [i]type inference[/i]. In many cases, but not all, the computer can figure out the type of a variable for you."
msgstr "GDScript 带有一个称为[i]类型推测[/i]（type inference）的功能。在多数情况，但不是全部的情况下，计算机可以替你确定变量的类型。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:72
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "To do so, you write [code]:=[/code], without the type. The computer will set the type using the value after the equal sign. We could make [code]cell_size[/code] a variable of type [code]Vector2[/code] like so:"
msgstr "为此，你只用写[code]:=[/code]，不用写类型。计算机将使用等号后面的值为依据来设置类型。这样也可以将[code]cell_size[/code]设为[code]Vector2[/code]类型的变量，如下所示："

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:75
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This takes little typing, yet you get the benefits of using type hints, like the computer reporting errors better and faster."
msgstr "这样你写的也少，也能得到变量类型提示功能的好处，比如能更好更快地报告类型错误。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:75
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "heading"
msgid "Why bother to add hints?"
msgstr "何必多写一个类型提示呢？"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:85
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "When you give the language hints like that, it will [i]prevent[/i] major type errors. When you work in Godot, you will see that the computer can report issues as you write the code. It makes the benefit even greater."
msgstr "当你给编程语言这些类型提示时，它能[i]防止[/i]大多数的类型错误。当你在用Godot时，计算机可以在写代码的时候实时反馈各种问题。使用类型提示就更有帮助了。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:86
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Type hints can also help improve the readability of your code. It can help to put more information directly in the code. As we saw, types are essential when coding, and when using type hints, the computer will add them to the engine's built-in code documentation system."
msgstr "类型提示还可以帮助提高代码的可读性。能让很多信息以直观的形式放在代码里。正如我们所看到的，活用类型在写代码时是必不可少的，当使用类型提示时，计算机就能对他们用上引擎内置的实时编程文档系统。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:87
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "There's an incredible third benefit for you: by using type hints, you will learn types much faster. It's excellent for learning."
msgstr "第三个好处，对你来说是好极了的：通过使用类型提示，你能更快地学习掌握不同的类型。对学习非常有益。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:88
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In the following practices, you will write the correct type hints to make the code error-free."
msgstr "在后续的练习中，我们将绘制多个角来创建矩形。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:85
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.0.title"
msgid "Add the correct type hints to variables"
msgstr "向变量添加正确的类型提示"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:85
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.0.goal"
msgid "Our variables get the correct values but not the right hints. Using your type-fu, add the correct type names in the variable definitions."
msgstr "我们的变量得到了正确的值，但是类型提示是错误的。用你刚学到的类型招式大展拳脚，为变量定义添加正确的类型名。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:85
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.0.goal"
msgid "You need to write the type name between the colon and the equal sign."
msgstr "在变量名和子变量名之间写一个点号（.）。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:85
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.0.goal"
msgid "Note: You cannot use type inference in this practice. You need to write the type name in full."
msgstr "注意：这个练习中使用类型推断功能被禁用了。需要你写出完整的类型名称。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:85
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.0.description"
msgid "Our variables have the wrong type hints, causing errors. Correct them to make the code run."
msgstr "变量的类型提示搞错了，就会导致错误。更正它们以使代码运行。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:105
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.1.title"
msgid "Fix the values to match the type hints"
msgstr "修改变量的值以匹配类型提示"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:105
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.1.goal"
msgid "It is the other way around in this practice: the type hints are fine, but the values are not."
msgstr "这个练习又和上次恰恰相反：类型提示好得很，但是变量的值有问题。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:105
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.1.goal"
msgid "Your task is to fix the values after the equal sign, so they match the type hint of each variable."
msgstr "你的任务是修改等号后的值，使它们与每个变量的类型提示相匹配。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:105
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "practice.1.description"
msgid "This time, it's the other way around: variables have the correct type hints but the wrong values. Change the values to make the code run."
msgstr "这次的情况正好相反：变量有正确的类型提示，但错误的值。 修改值以使代码运行。"

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:105
msgctxt "practice.1.hint"
msgid "The type [code]float[/code] means decimal number, so you need to write a number with a decimal part, like [code]3.14[/code]."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:105
msgctxt "practice.1.hint"
msgid "The type [code]int[/code] stands for integer or whole number, so you need the value to be a whole number without a decimal part."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-28-specifying-types/lesson.bbcode:105
msgctxt "practice.1.hint"
msgid "The type [code]String[/code] means you need to write a text string, a value surrounded by quotes."
msgstr ""

msgid "Learn to Code From Zero with Godot"
msgstr ""

msgid "Engineers at Tesla also used it for their cars' dashboards."
msgstr "特斯拉的工程师用它制作了汽车的仪表盘。"

msgid "We can use it to ensure that the changes between frames don't make the game's behavior unreliable."
msgstr "用它可以确保帧之间的变化不会使游戏的模拟变得不可靠。"

msgid ""
"100\n"
"75\n"
"50\n"
"25\n"
"0\n"
"-25"
msgstr ""
"100\n"
"75\n"
"50\n"
"25\n"
"0\n"
"-25"

msgid ""
"[code]>[/code] means \"greater than\"\n"
"[code]<[/code] means \"less than\"\n"
"[code]==[/code] means \"equal to\"\n"
"[code]!=[/code] means \"not equal to\""
msgstr ""
"[code]>[/code] 意思是“大于”\n"
"[code]<[/code] 意思是“小于”\n"
"[code]==[/code] 意思是“等于”\n"
"[code]!=[/code] 表示“不等于”"

msgid ""
"The comparison [code]3 > 1[/code] means \"three is greater than one\" which is [b]true[/b].\n"
"The comparison [code]2 < 3[/code] means \"two is less than three\" which is [b]true[/b].\n"
"The comparison [code]1 != 3[/code] means \"one is not equal to three\" which is [b]true[/b]."
msgstr ""
"[code]3 > 1[/code] 表示“三大于一”，为 [b]true[/b]。\n"
"[code]2 < 3[/code] 表示“二小于三”，为 [b]true[/b]。\n"
"[code]1 != 3[/code] 表示“一不等于三”，为 [b]true[/b]。"

msgid "This series of [code]if[/code] statements is all wrong. Change the comparisons so each comparison matches the instruction below it."
msgstr "这一系列的 [code]if[/code] 语句都是错误的。更改它们的比较语句，使每个比较语句与下面的文本指示的意思匹配。"

msgid "Keep the values and statements as they are; only change the comparison signs."
msgstr "不要改动具体的数值和句子的意思；只更改比较符号。"

msgid ""
"As a reminder, the comparison signs are:\n"
"[code]\n"
"> greater than\n"
"< less than\n"
"== equal to\n"
"!= not equal to\n"
"[/code]"
msgstr ""
"提醒一下，比较符号和对应的英文是：\n"
"[code]\n"
"> 大于 (greater than)\n"
"< 小于 (less than)\n"
"== 等于 (equal to)\n"
"!= 不等于 (not equal to)\n"
"[/code]"

msgid "Because [code]health = 100[/code], this is false so [code]print(\"health is greater than five.\")[/code] won't run."
msgstr "因为 [code]health = 100[/code]的比较结果是假（false），所以对应的 [code]print(\"health is greater than 5.\")[/code] 不会被运行。"

msgid "We have a heal function that adds an amount to the character's health."
msgstr "我们有一个治疗函数（heal），可以增加角色的生命值。"

msgid "Add to the function so the character's health is never greater than [code]80[/code]."
msgstr "补全函数，使角色的生命值永远不会超过 [code]80[/code]。"

msgid "When the robot takes damage, its health can be negative."
msgstr "当机器人受到伤害时，它的血量/生命值可能变成负的。"

msgid "We might want to display the health number on screen, like in Japanese RPGs."
msgstr "我们也许想在屏幕上显示出血量的数值，类似日式RPG（JRPG） 那样。"

msgid "We don't want negative numbers. We want to stop at zero instead."
msgstr "我们不希望出现负数。相反，我们希望扣血时会停在零。"

msgid "Our robot's health is always between [code]0[/code] and [code]100[/code]."
msgstr "我们机器人的血量状况始终介于 [code]0[/code] 和 [code]100[/code] 之间。"

msgid "But as our robot fights, we want to increase its strength and toughness."
msgstr "但是当我们的机器人战斗时，我们想要增加它的力量和韧性。"

msgid "When a character levels up, it might deal more damage to enemies, gain new abilities or, in our case, gain more health."
msgstr "当一个角色升级时，它可能会对敌人造成更多伤害，获得新的能力，或者在我们的例子中，获得更多的血量。"

msgid ""
"[code]\n"
"var level = 5\n"
"var power = 3"
msgstr ""
"[code]\n"
"var level = 5\n"
"var power = 3"

msgid "However, they could result in infinite loops if we're not careful."
msgstr "但是，如果够不小心，它可能会导致无限循环/死循环。"

msgid "Rather than constantly checking if the robot reached the end of the board, with the [code]for[/code] loop, we take the board's width beforehand, then move the robot a set amount of times."
msgstr "与其不断检查机器人是否到达棋盘末端，我们用 [code]for[/code] 循环，预先获取棋盘的宽度，然后让机器人移动一定的次数就好了。"

msgid "Populate the combo array with animation names as strings."
msgstr "把不同动画名称的字符串，填充进数组里。"

msgid "The array should contain three values, so the robot makes these three attacks: two jabs followed by one uppercut."
msgstr "字符串数组应包含三个变量，由此机器人会按顺序执行以下操作：jab、jab、uppercut。"

msgid "You can assign the return value of a function call if you plan on using it more than once."
msgstr "如果你计划多次使用一个函数的返回值的话，你可以将它赋值给一个变量。"

msgid "It takes three arguments: the two values to average and a value between [code]0.0[/code] and [code]1.0[/code] to skew the result."
msgstr "它需要三个参数：要平均的两个值，和一个 [code]0.0[/code] 和 [code]1.0[/code] 之间的值来偏移结果（和小的值更近还是和大的更近）。"

msgid "In game programming, it's used to animate things moving towards a target with a single line of code."
msgstr "在游戏编程中，用它只需一行代码，就能使物体向一个目标运动起来。"

msgid "In previous lessons, we had characters walking on grids."
msgstr "在之前的课程中，我们成功让角色能在棋盘网格上行走。"

msgid "And for those practices, you were working directly with cell coordinates."
msgstr "在那些练习中，你直接使用的是网格本身的单元坐标。"

msgid "Well, cell coordinates don't correspond to positions on the screen. To find the center of any cell on the screen, we need to convert the cell's coordinates to a position on the screen, in pixels."
msgstr "但是呢，单元格坐标和屏幕上的位置并不是对应的，所以我们需要将单元格位置转换为屏幕上的像素位置。"

msgid "To do so, we use a function. The function does two things:"
msgstr "为此，我们要用到一个函数。该函数应有两个功能："

msgid ""
"1. First, it multiplies the cell coordinates by the cell size, which gives us the position of the cell's top-left corner on the screen, in pixels.\n"
"2. Then, we add half of the cell size to get the center of the cell."
msgstr ""
"第一步，它将单元格坐标乘以单元格大小，得出单元格的左上角在屏幕上的位置（以像素为单位）。\n"
"第二步，加上一个单元格的大小的二分之一，得到单元格的中心点的位置。"

msgid "In this example, we simulate orders arriving and getting completed over time."
msgstr "这个例子中，我们模拟了一种订单模式，按时间推移会出现订单，紧接着会被完成。"

msgid "The value in question could be the crate's content, which you can then use to give resources to the player."
msgstr "函数找到的值可以是箱子里装的具体的内容，然后你就可以使用这个栈来为玩家提供资源。"

msgid "Like with arrays, you can loop over dictionaries. You can loop over both their keys and values."
msgstr "和数组一样，你能够遍历字典。 遍历它的key（键，关键）和对应的值。"

msgid "But it's something we do so much that you don't need to call the function."
msgstr "但这个功能我们用的太频繁了，以至于现在都不需要调用该函数。"

msgid "The instructions inside the function [b]must[/b] all start with a leading tab character. You can insert that tab character by pressing the [b]Tab[/b] key."
msgstr "函数中的指令 [b] 必须[/b] 都以“前导制表符”开头。 你可以通过按 [b]Tab[/b] 键插入该制表符。"

msgid "We call those leading tabs [i]indents[/i]. They're important: the computer uses them to know which instructions are part of the same code block."
msgstr "我们将这些“前导制表符”称为 [i] 缩进 [/i]。 它们很重要：计算机使用它们来分清楚哪些指令是属于同一个代码块。"

msgid "Can I rotate in both directions?"
msgstr "我可以向两个方向旋转吗？"

msgid "The [code]radians[/code] can be a positive or negative number, which allows you to rotate both clockwise and counter-clockwise."
msgstr "[code]radians[/code] 可以是正数或负数，它允许你顺时针和逆时针旋转。"

msgid "Wherever the computer sees the identifier [code]radians[/code] inside the function, it replaces it with the [code]0.5[/code] value."
msgstr "计算机在函数内任何地方看到标识符 [code]radians[/code]，都会将其替换为 [code]0.5[/code] 。"

msgid "The parameter name is always a label you use to refer to a [i]value[/i]. The value in question can be a number, text, or anything else."
msgstr "参数名称始终是你用来引用 [i] 值[/i] 的标签。 这些值可以是数字、文本或其他任何内容。"

msgid "For now, we'll stick to numbers as we have yet to see other value types."
msgstr "目前，我们只使用数字，因为我们还没有接触到其他类型的值。"

msgid "A parameter is a label that represents a value."
msgstr "参数是表示值的标签。"

msgid "Parameters make your code easier to reuse."
msgstr "参数使你的代码更易于重复使用。"

msgid "Here we have an incomplete function that will draw corners with lines of any length, but it's missing its [code]length[/code] parameter."
msgstr "这里我们有一个不完整的函数，它可以用任意长度的线画直角，但是它缺少它的 [code]length[/code] 参数。"

msgid "We could use these squares as outlines when selecting units in a tactical game, as a frame for items in an inventory, and more."
msgstr "我们可以将这些正方形用作战术游戏中选择单位时出现的轮廓，背包中物品显示的边框等等。"

msgid "[b]The turtle should face towards the right when starting or completing a square.[/b]"
msgstr "[b]开始或画完一个矩形时，乌龟应该面向右侧。[/b]"

msgid "Be sure to call [b]turn_right(90)[/b]  enough times in your function to do so."
msgstr "为到达上述效果，请确保在你的函数中调用足够次的 [b]turn_right(90)[/b] 函数。"

msgid "Let's make our square drawing function more flexible to include rectangles of varying sizes."
msgstr "让我们来把矩形绘图功能做得更加灵活，能画出各种各样的矩形。"

msgid "[b]The turtle should face towards the right when starting or completing a rectangle.[/b]"
msgstr "[b]开始或画完一个矩形时，乌龟应该面向右侧。[/b]"

msgid "Note that we could still draw a square with [code]draw_rectangle()[/code] by having the [code]length[/code] and [code]height[/code] equal the same value."
msgstr "要留意我们还是可以用 [code]draw_rectangle()[/code]绘制正方形，给 [code]length[/code] 和 [code]height[/code] 相同的值就行了。"
